                                                                                                        Keyword
1.this Keyword (Current Object Reference)
Definition
↬ this is a reference variable that refers to the current object of the class.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------↬ Whenever a method or constructor is called on an object, Java internally passes that object’s reference as this.

Example:-
class Solution{
int roll;
Solution(int roll){
this.roll=roll;
}

void display(){
System.out.println(roll);
 }
public static void main(String [] args){
Solution s=new Solution(101);
s.display();
 }
}

◍ Why needed?
Without this, Java gives priority to local variables.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
➲ To Call Current Class Method
class Demo {
    void show() {
        System.out.println("Show method");
    }

    void display() {
        this.show();   // optional but valid
    }
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
➲ To Pass Current Object as Argument
class A {
    void show(A obj) {
        System.out.println("Method called");
    }

    void call() {
        show(this);
    }
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
➲ To Pass Current Object as Argument
class A {
    void show(A obj) {
        System.out.println("Method called");
    }

    void call() {
        show(this);
    }
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
➲ To Call Current Class Constructor (Constructor Chaining)
class Test {
    Test() {
        this(10);   // calls parameterized constructor
        System.out.println("Default constructor");
    }

    Test(int a) {
        System.out.println("Parameterized constructor: " + a);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new Test();
    }
}
 Rule: this() must be the first statement in constructor.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
★ Key Rules for this
➙ Refers to current object
➙ Cannot be used in static context
➙ Improves readability
➙ Used only inside instance methods/constructors

